WEBVTT

00:18.496 --> 00:22.065
Do you get used to that, too?
Taking orders from a camera?

00:22.196 --> 00:23.501
Not yet.

00:23.632 --> 00:25.547
Management trusts
you will come to them

00:25.677 --> 00:27.114
the moment you have something.

00:27.244 --> 00:28.506
Of course.

00:28.637 --> 00:31.379
[ speaking German ]

00:31.509 --> 00:32.467
MIRA:
You have the case?

00:32.597 --> 00:34.295
Yes.

00:34.425 --> 00:36.558
There's someone else at Echo?

00:36.688 --> 00:38.212
Someone important?

00:38.342 --> 00:40.605
These were my friends once.

00:40.736 --> 00:43.608
We had come of age
behind the Wall,

00:43.739 --> 00:47.003
only to discover
the existence of two worlds.

00:47.134 --> 00:48.526
May I tell you a secret?

00:48.657 --> 00:50.659
Something just for you.

00:50.789 --> 00:54.750
I am the reason
our two worlds exist.

00:57.318 --> 00:59.842
[ speaking German ]

01:06.631 --> 01:08.590
CROFT:
It's a Minox C.

01:08.720 --> 01:11.723
Most popular camera
in the city these days.

01:11.854 --> 01:14.987
You have five rolls,
36 exposures each.

01:15.118 --> 01:18.165
Keep it somewhere safe
and out of sight.

01:18.295 --> 01:20.384
Needless to say,
if you get caught with it,

01:20.515 --> 01:22.082
you're on your own.

01:22.212 --> 01:25.172
Will we cross in the city?

01:25.302 --> 01:27.391
No. We're getting you out
through Heiligensee.

01:27.522 --> 01:29.698
It's a Trabi
with a false floor in back.

01:29.828 --> 01:33.223
Your son and daughter inside,
you and your wife up front.

01:33.354 --> 01:36.400
I never thought
it would be this way.

01:36.531 --> 01:39.534
Think about your son's safety.

01:41.013 --> 01:43.712
You're doing the right thing.

01:43.842 --> 01:48.282
My father died in the camps
for a democratic republic.

01:48.412 --> 01:49.587
You didn't fail him, Yanek.

01:49.718 --> 01:51.198
Honecker failed him.

01:51.328 --> 01:52.460
The whole institution
failed him.

01:52.590 --> 01:53.504
Yes.

01:55.202 --> 01:57.987
The experiment was perfect.

01:58.118 --> 01:59.554
It was corrupted
by our pettiness.

02:01.599 --> 02:03.123
24 hours.

02:03.253 --> 02:05.560
Bring us details
of the synchotron,

02:05.690 --> 02:08.519
heat output, collated angles
and trajectories.

02:08.650 --> 02:10.695
This time next month,

02:10.826 --> 02:13.176
you and your family'll be
watching American baseball.

02:15.047 --> 02:15.874
[ bicycle bell rings ]

02:17.267 --> 02:19.530
♪

02:38.549 --> 02:40.856
[ speaking German indistinctly ]

02:45.382 --> 02:48.255
[ playing faintly ]
♪ There's no reason to hurry

02:48.385 --> 02:50.779
♪ Just start the brand-new
story, set it alight ♪

02:50.909 --> 02:52.302
Aren't you ever sick
of that song?

02:52.433 --> 02:54.086
Alphaville's the best.

02:54.217 --> 02:55.087
Turn it down.

02:55.218 --> 02:56.567
You turn it down.

02:56.698 --> 02:58.569
ISABELL:
Mira,

02:58.700 --> 03:00.397
turn your music down.

03:00.528 --> 03:03.052
♪ To once-forbidden place... ♪

03:05.576 --> 03:07.970
[ quietly ]
They've given me a camera.

03:08.100 --> 03:10.059
When does it happen?

03:10.190 --> 03:11.147
Soon.

03:17.936 --> 03:19.155
YANEK:
Take your medication.

03:19.286 --> 03:21.244
Makes me dizzy before I eat.

03:21.375 --> 03:23.072
ISABELL:
Well, eat some Filinchen.

03:23.203 --> 03:25.074
No, I'm sick of Filinchen.

03:25.205 --> 03:27.424
Mmm. I love crispy bread.

03:27.555 --> 03:29.339
You would.

03:29.470 --> 03:31.428
None of this crap here
has any flavor.

03:31.559 --> 03:34.692
Herr Hauser says only fascists
complain about flavor.

03:34.823 --> 03:36.259
Hauser's a Stasi stooge.

03:38.783 --> 03:40.785
What? It isn't true?

03:40.916 --> 03:43.440
Don't speak
against our comrades.

03:43.571 --> 03:45.573
It's unpatriotic.

03:45.703 --> 03:47.139
He made a report
about Frau Stein.

03:47.270 --> 03:48.140
-Did you know that?
-And what business

03:48.271 --> 03:50.317
is that of yours?

03:50.447 --> 03:52.884
Do you even know how to shit
without the party telling you?

03:53.015 --> 03:54.669
-What did you say?
-It's all right.

03:54.799 --> 03:56.323
You have no idea the sacrifices
your father makes

03:56.453 --> 03:57.715
to keep you out of trouble.

03:57.846 --> 04:01.545
Those antisocial friends
you run around with.

04:03.591 --> 04:05.941
At least they believe
in something.

04:11.555 --> 04:13.035
[ door slams ]

04:26.962 --> 04:28.877
-[ indistinct chatter ]
-[ horn honking ]

04:29.007 --> 04:30.531
WOMAN: Please hurry up.
We're gonna be late.

04:30.661 --> 04:32.620
♪

04:44.893 --> 04:47.156
[ indistinct chatter ]

04:49.724 --> 04:51.465
[ man speaking indistinctly
over phone ]

04:58.602 --> 05:00.648
-[ phones ringing ]
-[ indistinct chatter ]

05:02.867 --> 05:03.999
-Is that right?
-Yeah.

05:05.827 --> 05:07.524
...so I had to go
to the store after work.

05:07.655 --> 05:09.787
I finally get inside,
and I look around.

05:09.918 --> 05:11.180
There's nothing left.

05:11.311 --> 05:12.616
Nothing but pickles.

05:12.747 --> 05:14.923
So I ask the store manager
and he says,

05:15.053 --> 05:17.273
"Why do we need happiness
when we have so many pickles?"

05:17.404 --> 05:19.188
YANEK: [ clears throat ]
I've madesome changes

05:19.319 --> 05:20.842
to the X-ray splitter.

05:20.972 --> 05:22.931
Should get rid
of that nasty bug.

05:23.061 --> 05:25.237
-Please recalibrate it.
-That'll take me all day.

05:25.368 --> 05:27.327
And?

05:30.982 --> 05:33.681
[ indistinct chatter ]

05:36.031 --> 05:38.033
-[ bell rings ]
-WOMAN: Okay, time to go.

05:38.163 --> 05:40.427
-MAN: See you tomorrow.
-Bye!

05:40.557 --> 05:43.255
-WOMAN 2: Tomorrow.
-[ indistinct chatter ]

05:50.393 --> 05:51.220
[ door closes ]

06:01.752 --> 06:04.712
♪

06:09.717 --> 06:12.067
[ steady beeping ]

06:15.636 --> 06:18.073
[ shutter clicks ]

06:23.557 --> 06:24.732
[ whirring, clacking ]

06:26.560 --> 06:28.736
[ shutter clicking ]

06:30.520 --> 06:31.391
[ shattering in distance ]

06:32.609 --> 06:34.089
[ squeaking ]

06:44.926 --> 06:47.276
[ printers clacking ]

06:55.850 --> 06:58.200
[ clacking, steady beeping ]

07:09.472 --> 07:11.692
[ beeping ]

07:14.782 --> 07:17.132
[ electricity buzzing ]

07:19.569 --> 07:20.831
[ rattling ]

07:20.962 --> 07:23.355
[ whirring ]

07:23.486 --> 07:26.533
[ beeping ]

07:26.663 --> 07:28.622
[ hissing ]

07:31.407 --> 07:33.627
[ rumbling, clattering ]

07:37.326 --> 07:39.937
[ rattling ]

07:40.068 --> 07:42.331
-[ beeping ]
-[ electricity buzzing ]

07:50.774 --> 07:52.428
-[ rumbling ]
-[ alarm blaring ]

08:00.480 --> 08:03.483
[ alarm blaring ]

08:20.021 --> 08:22.371
[ electricity crackling ]

08:27.115 --> 08:30.510
[ cracking, crumbling ]

08:37.168 --> 08:38.909
[ electricity buzzing ]

08:39.040 --> 08:40.781
[ panting ]

08:40.911 --> 08:42.217
[ gasps, grunts ]

08:47.701 --> 08:49.877
[ Yanek panting ]

08:56.797 --> 08:59.582
[ echoing ]
Hello?

09:01.149 --> 09:04.239
Is someone there?

09:08.983 --> 09:11.376
Who is it?

09:23.432 --> 09:25.260
[ both gasping ]

09:27.697 --> 09:29.264
[ panting ]

09:34.965 --> 09:36.924
♪

10:04.386 --> 10:07.302
♪

10:33.763 --> 10:35.678
♪

10:57.004 --> 10:58.658
[ birds chirping ]

10:58.788 --> 11:00.660
[ bees buzzing ]

11:08.885 --> 11:11.061
[ door creaking ]

11:17.285 --> 11:20.157
I used to bring you here.

11:20.288 --> 11:23.160
Wasn't me you brought.

11:23.291 --> 11:26.120
Wasn't here you brought her.

11:27.338 --> 11:30.559
This is where you live now?

11:31.734 --> 11:33.562
I move around a lot.

11:33.693 --> 11:34.781
Why?

11:47.054 --> 11:49.404
Because I'm being hunted.

11:52.886 --> 11:56.585
This is who my daughter
has become?

11:56.716 --> 11:58.935
I'm not your daughter.

12:00.328 --> 12:02.896
I made you into this.

12:03.026 --> 12:05.855
Don't talk about me like
I'm your fucking experiment.

12:05.986 --> 12:09.032
-You were never
any such thing to me.
-Yes, I was.

12:09.163 --> 12:10.164
I've read all about it.

12:14.864 --> 12:16.431
Right here.

12:18.650 --> 12:20.870
Where did you find this?

12:21.001 --> 12:23.046
Your world.

12:23.177 --> 12:25.483
Wasn't hard to acquire.

12:28.748 --> 12:31.098
I have people there--

12:31.228 --> 12:32.969
an army--

12:33.100 --> 12:35.667
inspired by your words,

12:35.798 --> 12:37.234
your feelings,

12:37.365 --> 12:39.106
your deepest confessions.

12:40.934 --> 12:43.153
What do you want from me?

12:51.814 --> 12:53.381
Rest.

12:53.511 --> 12:55.470
We have a lot to discuss.

13:01.563 --> 13:03.521
♪

13:11.965 --> 13:13.836
YANEK:
Maybe we should have run.

13:13.967 --> 13:16.752
That would have been
the smarter thing.

13:16.883 --> 13:18.101
But we were scientists

13:18.232 --> 13:20.625
and experimentalists.

13:20.756 --> 13:23.498
We were, above all things...

13:23.628 --> 13:24.673
curious.

13:26.457 --> 13:28.895
[ deep, echoing creaking ]

13:34.857 --> 13:37.251
[ deep creaking continues ]

13:41.429 --> 13:43.605
Who are you?

13:45.694 --> 13:47.217
Speak.

13:50.133 --> 13:51.526
MAN:
Did I create you?

13:53.180 --> 13:55.138
Because I left my post.

13:55.269 --> 13:58.098
Ran the program
so I could be upstairs.

13:58.228 --> 13:59.229
I created you.

13:59.360 --> 14:00.883
Nonsense.

14:01.014 --> 14:03.799
-I left my post.
-No, you didn't.

14:03.930 --> 14:05.757
Why are you imitating
the words I say?

14:11.024 --> 14:13.853
Would you like
to come over and talk?

14:15.724 --> 14:18.727
[ alarm blaring ]

14:21.121 --> 14:23.993
-[ clanking, thumping ]
-[ alarm stops ]

14:24.124 --> 14:25.603
[ power whirring ]

14:54.284 --> 14:55.590
Something must have happened

14:55.720 --> 14:58.071
when the particles divided
and went into superposition.

14:58.201 --> 15:00.029
A quantum mechanical
entanglement.

15:00.160 --> 15:03.206
I'll have to see if anything's
left back there to analyze.

15:11.388 --> 15:13.347
Tell me what I'm thinking.

15:15.566 --> 15:17.612
My eyes are too close together.

15:17.742 --> 15:19.222
My nose?

15:19.353 --> 15:22.225
Too large. My father's nose.

15:23.923 --> 15:25.837
We're the same.

15:25.968 --> 15:28.057
Identical.

15:28.188 --> 15:30.886
A world for you...

15:31.017 --> 15:32.932
and a world for me?

15:33.062 --> 15:35.586
And what do we do now?

15:35.717 --> 15:37.762
♪

15:41.027 --> 15:43.072
That was when we knew

15:43.203 --> 15:47.033
leaving the East
was no longer an option.

15:47.163 --> 15:49.035
Tell me you're fucking
with me. Seriously?

15:49.165 --> 15:51.820
I-I just need a few more weeks.

15:52.908 --> 15:54.127
Yanek...

15:54.257 --> 15:56.259
do you realize for one moment

15:56.390 --> 15:58.131
how hard it is
to secure an exfil

15:58.261 --> 16:00.133
with eyes on you
and your family?

16:00.263 --> 16:03.136
Your son was photographed
the other day at Zionskirche

16:03.266 --> 16:05.051
handing out subversive leaflets.

16:05.181 --> 16:07.183
Treason against the state.
This is not the time

16:07.314 --> 16:08.880
-for cold feet.
-It's not cold feet.

16:09.011 --> 16:10.839
Then what the hell has changed?

16:12.232 --> 16:14.364
-I just need more time.
-[ scoffs ]

16:21.197 --> 16:24.635
In 72 hours, that car is gone.

16:24.766 --> 16:27.290
If you and your family
aren't there...

16:27.421 --> 16:30.467
there will not be another.

16:30.598 --> 16:33.122
Just think
about what you're doing.

16:33.253 --> 16:36.169
Do you really want to be
at the mercy of your comrades?

16:37.387 --> 16:39.346
♪

16:46.135 --> 16:48.181
YANEK:
With the synchrotron down,

16:48.311 --> 16:50.966
everyone understood the lab
would be closed for repairs.

16:51.097 --> 16:55.710
Those lifeless drones were glad
for the time off.

16:55.840 --> 16:58.408
They would take long lunches,
go home to their families,

16:58.539 --> 17:01.368
and inside those walls,

17:01.498 --> 17:04.066
our study would begin.

17:04.197 --> 17:06.329
YANEK PRIME:
Look at that.

17:06.460 --> 17:09.463
I'm still getting
a lot of radiation.

17:12.422 --> 17:14.990
YANEK:
We resolved to keep journals.

17:15.121 --> 17:18.385
Like humble socialists
who had found themselves

17:18.515 --> 17:20.691
the subjects of their own
exhaustive study.

17:20.822 --> 17:24.173
Even the smallest imperfections
were shared between us.

17:24.304 --> 17:26.001
-I have this chip, too.
-Yes, right here.

17:26.132 --> 17:28.308
-It's on this one, right?
-Right. That's right.

17:28.438 --> 17:30.832
YANEK: Whatever process
had created us,

17:30.962 --> 17:34.096
it was meticulous.

17:34.227 --> 17:35.489
We were identical.

17:35.619 --> 17:38.361
And likewise,

17:38.492 --> 17:41.016
so were our worlds.

17:43.932 --> 17:47.196
[ static ]

17:47.327 --> 17:50.765
WOMAN [ over both radios ]:
...in the Battle of Berlin...

17:50.895 --> 17:53.376
YANEK PRIME: They've doubled
in number lately.

17:53.507 --> 17:56.162
They're exploring
each other's territory.

17:56.292 --> 17:58.686
Yes, I think so.

17:58.816 --> 18:01.471
YANEK: I've been thinking
about something.

18:01.602 --> 18:05.910
If it's all right,
I'd like to see your world.

18:06.041 --> 18:09.523
I'd like to see yours, too.

18:15.268 --> 18:17.096
[ indistinct chatter ]

18:22.275 --> 18:23.406
YANEK:
It was like walking through

18:23.537 --> 18:25.104
a perfect reproduction.

18:25.234 --> 18:26.931
[ bicycle bell rings ]

18:28.194 --> 18:31.240
It was a miracle.

18:31.371 --> 18:36.158
His world was impossible
to differentiate,

18:36.289 --> 18:40.075
down to the most minute detail.

18:43.078 --> 18:45.472
♪

18:50.041 --> 18:52.696
And that was the problem.

18:52.827 --> 18:55.830
It was exactly the same.

18:55.960 --> 18:59.529
If this experiment were
to have any impact,

18:59.660 --> 19:02.837
something drastic
had to be done.

19:10.758 --> 19:12.586
[ both chuckle ]

19:12.716 --> 19:16.285
For Mira.
She loves this music.

19:16.416 --> 19:18.331
I wanted to see if you would
make the same choice.

19:27.775 --> 19:30.038
What are you doing?

19:30.169 --> 19:32.606
You give your daughter
your gift.

19:32.736 --> 19:34.085
I'll give nothing to mine.

19:34.216 --> 19:36.523
Make our worlds different.

19:36.653 --> 19:40.657
Manufacture a control and chaos.

19:40.788 --> 19:44.183
I think you're right.

19:44.313 --> 19:47.447
YANEK:
And so it was decided.

19:47.577 --> 19:50.972
From that point on,
there was no going back.

19:53.409 --> 19:56.107
GIRL: Mommy, come on,
I want to go home.

19:56.238 --> 19:58.501
YANEK:
With one simple adjustment,

19:58.632 --> 20:03.202
we would set our worlds on two
irreversibly different paths.

20:13.124 --> 20:15.605
-Hello, Mira.
-Hello.

20:15.736 --> 20:17.433
I have something for you.

20:17.564 --> 20:19.566
Hello.

20:19.696 --> 20:20.654
I think you're going to like it.

20:20.784 --> 20:22.438
Hi.

20:24.440 --> 20:26.225
-Did you have a good day?
-Mm-hmm.

20:26.355 --> 20:29.228
-You like this band, right?
-I love it.

20:29.358 --> 20:32.492
-Thank you.
-Oh. [ laughs ]

20:32.622 --> 20:35.973
Yeah. I love you.

20:43.764 --> 20:45.896
YANEK:
If only we'd known

20:46.027 --> 20:48.986
the impact we were about
to make.

21:01.869 --> 21:05.089
How long have I been asleep?

21:05.220 --> 21:07.527
A few hours.

21:07.657 --> 21:09.703
Thought I'd let you rest.

21:20.235 --> 21:21.410
[ case beeps ]

21:24.370 --> 21:26.720
What is that?

21:26.850 --> 21:29.375
Belongs to your friends
in Management.

21:29.505 --> 21:32.769
They use it to communicate
in each world.

21:32.900 --> 21:35.337
They never meet in person.

21:35.468 --> 21:37.339
Not since what you did.

21:39.167 --> 21:41.125
It's war, now.

21:41.256 --> 21:43.084
-And you are part of it?
-No.

21:44.825 --> 21:49.395
But you and I,
we are going to end it.

21:49.525 --> 21:52.876
I've been planting soldiers
in their world for years.

21:53.007 --> 21:54.835
A few weeks ago,
we got their attention,

21:54.965 --> 21:59.579
and now, I need
for your friends to meet.

21:59.709 --> 22:01.407
Why?

22:01.537 --> 22:03.191
So they can do what
they should have done

22:03.322 --> 22:05.324
many years ago.

22:09.893 --> 22:12.069
End this experiment forever.

22:20.426 --> 22:21.644
Ah, you're so annoying.

22:28.564 --> 22:29.565
ISABELL:
Yanek.

22:35.049 --> 22:37.834
Did something happen
to the arrangement?

22:37.965 --> 22:39.140
Let's not talk about this now.

22:40.663 --> 22:42.273
Last week you said next week.

22:42.404 --> 22:44.101
Every day, another excuse.

22:46.016 --> 22:48.018
Our departure has been delayed.

22:48.149 --> 22:50.369
-For how long?
-I don't know yet.

22:50.499 --> 22:52.196
What happened?

22:52.327 --> 22:53.372
What will we do?

22:53.502 --> 22:54.808
I can't be bothered by this now.

22:54.938 --> 22:56.897
What is this?

22:57.027 --> 22:58.899
I don't like how
you've been acting.

22:59.029 --> 23:00.553
How have I been acting, Isabell?

23:00.683 --> 23:03.120
I don't know, not yourself.

23:03.251 --> 23:04.383
And how is myself?

23:04.513 --> 23:07.037
Unhappy?

23:07.168 --> 23:09.518
Because for years
I've had no purpose.

23:09.649 --> 23:12.608
Just a loyalist
to a dying system.

23:12.739 --> 23:14.480
Now that I have purpose again,
you don't like me.

23:14.610 --> 23:15.829
What purpose?

23:15.959 --> 23:17.091
What are you talking about?

23:18.962 --> 23:20.529
I have to go.

23:23.880 --> 23:26.361
YANEK: I couldn't be bothered
by such things.

23:26.492 --> 23:29.843
Not when our endeavor
was beginning to grow.

23:29.973 --> 23:32.367
This building housed
an experimental synchrotron,

23:32.498 --> 23:36.545
used various light sources
to divide particles.

23:36.676 --> 23:39.983
Until recently, that is.

23:40.114 --> 23:42.856
Now the whole experiment's
changed.

23:42.986 --> 23:44.597
What happened
to all your assistants?

23:44.727 --> 23:47.382
Yanek has probably
scared them off.

23:47.513 --> 23:49.253
YANEK:
They've been given furlough.

23:49.384 --> 23:53.170
My work has grown more...

23:53.301 --> 23:55.216
sensitive lately.

23:57.566 --> 24:00.351
That's what I wanted you to see.

24:00.482 --> 24:03.267
[ door opens ]

24:31.600 --> 24:33.646
♪

24:33.776 --> 24:36.736
Such a pleasure to meet you.

24:40.261 --> 24:41.654
YANEK PRIME:
All of you we've chosen

24:41.784 --> 24:43.569
because of your discipline.

24:43.699 --> 24:47.747
Martin, economics.
Juma, immunology.

24:47.877 --> 24:50.489
Ilse, environmental science.

24:50.619 --> 24:53.187
And Volker, human behavior.

24:54.231 --> 24:56.451
What we are presented with

24:56.582 --> 24:58.758
is an opportunity

24:58.888 --> 25:02.501
unique in the history
of our species.

25:02.631 --> 25:03.806
There will, of course, be terms.

25:03.937 --> 25:08.463
First, the secret
comes before our lives.

25:08.594 --> 25:10.857
We must protect it from getting
in the wrong hands.

25:10.987 --> 25:13.816
Second, none of us may meddle
in the lives of our echo.

25:13.947 --> 25:16.079
We are not our other.

25:16.210 --> 25:18.517
Our other is not us.

25:18.647 --> 25:22.782
We must remain discreet
to ourselves.

25:22.912 --> 25:25.045
It's a living petri dish.

25:25.175 --> 25:27.830
We can study the baseline
of human psychology.

25:27.961 --> 25:32.095
Yanek... are you sure
this is a good idea?

25:32.226 --> 25:33.270
We're talking about

25:33.401 --> 25:35.621
a parallel universe that,
for all we know,

25:35.751 --> 25:37.666
was never meant to be detected.

25:37.797 --> 25:39.973
I think the opportunities
outweigh the risks.

25:40.103 --> 25:43.106
If we do this,
it must be unanimous.

25:43.237 --> 25:46.501
There can't be
a single one of us left out.

25:47.676 --> 25:49.896
I know you want this.

25:50.026 --> 25:51.811
And do you know how?

25:56.685 --> 25:59.819
Because I want this, too.

25:59.949 --> 26:02.561
We all want this, don't we?

26:10.917 --> 26:12.571
On behalf of our world,

26:14.224 --> 26:16.009
it'll be an honor

26:16.139 --> 26:17.576
to work with you.

26:28.195 --> 26:30.110
[ "Der Blaue Planet"
by Karat playing ]

26:30.240 --> 26:31.720
YANEK PRIME: Okay,
we're ready. Just press it.

26:31.851 --> 26:32.808
Okay, come on.
Okay, quick, quick.

26:34.418 --> 26:36.290
Ready?

26:38.292 --> 26:40.033
YANEK:
We had come together

26:40.163 --> 26:42.470
in the benevolent spirit
of human science.

26:44.864 --> 26:47.649
Using Martin's connections
at the university,

26:47.780 --> 26:49.303
we were able
to persuade the state

26:49.433 --> 26:52.088
to close off the building
to all prying eyes.

26:56.397 --> 26:58.486
Our experiment
grew exponentially

26:58.617 --> 27:00.227
over those months.

27:00.357 --> 27:02.533
The advent
of microscopic adjustments

27:02.664 --> 27:05.624
in our biology,
history, environment.

27:05.754 --> 27:09.845
Impacted by an adaptive delta
we could only begin to grasp.

27:09.976 --> 27:11.542
It was thrilling.

27:11.673 --> 27:13.240
-Good morning.
-JUMA: How are you?

27:13.370 --> 27:15.198
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

27:15.329 --> 27:18.332
Your plant is right here.

27:20.943 --> 27:23.598
YANEK: There were no longer
limits to our discipline.

27:23.729 --> 27:25.121
We could study anything.

27:25.252 --> 27:26.949
We could pluck
botanical specimens

27:27.080 --> 27:28.821
from the same garden
in two worlds,

27:28.951 --> 27:31.258
and then we could build
entirely new ecosystems

27:31.388 --> 27:33.347
from the best
surviving samples.

27:33.477 --> 27:36.698
Not to mention psychology,
branches of human behavior,

27:36.829 --> 27:39.179
the study of world events
on a granular level.

27:39.309 --> 27:41.921
It was a time of discovery

27:42.051 --> 27:45.664
unlike anything since the dawn
of the New World.

27:53.976 --> 27:56.022
You always touch it like that.

27:56.152 --> 27:57.937
You might contaminate
the sample.

27:58.067 --> 27:59.982
Stop being so self-critical.

28:00.113 --> 28:01.244
YANEK:
We were friends.

28:01.375 --> 28:02.985
[ chuckles softly ]

28:03.116 --> 28:05.727
Brothers and sisters
for a common good.

28:07.294 --> 28:08.991
And then...

28:09.122 --> 28:10.906
[ knocking on door ]

28:22.265 --> 28:24.703
What time is it?

28:24.833 --> 28:26.705
[ knocking continues ]

28:26.835 --> 28:29.533
MAN:
Open the door.

28:35.975 --> 28:37.803
Dr. Tomes?

28:37.933 --> 28:39.630
Yes?

28:39.761 --> 28:41.458
Is your son home?

28:45.462 --> 28:47.900
ISABELL: Please, please,
there's a misunderstanding.

28:48.030 --> 28:49.292
I've done nothing wrong.

28:49.423 --> 28:51.947
It's better if you don't speak.

28:52.078 --> 28:53.427
Our son is innocent,
listen to him.

28:53.557 --> 28:55.603
-He's-he's done nothing.
-INSPECTOR: Really?

28:55.734 --> 28:58.954
Maybe this is not
his literature?

28:59.085 --> 29:00.695
Maybe it's yours.

29:00.826 --> 29:02.610
Or your daughter's.

29:02.741 --> 29:04.960
But I doubt that,

29:05.091 --> 29:06.048
because none of you
were photographed

29:06.179 --> 29:07.702
at Zionskirche as recently

29:07.833 --> 29:09.965
as two days ago.

29:10.096 --> 29:11.314
-[ grunts ]
-Isabell!

29:11.445 --> 29:13.316
You've brought such shame
to this family.

29:13.447 --> 29:14.665
-[ music playing loudly ]
-YANEK: Isabell, please...

29:14.796 --> 29:16.711
♪ I'll be just a step away

29:16.842 --> 29:17.799
♪ Now far away ♪

29:17.930 --> 29:19.845
Who do you think you are?

29:19.975 --> 29:21.760
Coming to my home?

29:21.890 --> 29:23.370
Do you even know who I am?

29:23.500 --> 29:24.588
-Take him out of here.
-RAINER: Get off of me!

29:24.719 --> 29:25.851
[ grunting ]

29:25.981 --> 29:27.330
-Please, you're hurting him!
-I have j--

29:27.461 --> 29:28.592
I have just been given
a university grant.

29:28.723 --> 29:30.333
Important work is being done

29:30.464 --> 29:31.552
on behalf of the party
and the people.

29:31.682 --> 29:33.684
-[ straining, grunting ]
-INSPECTOR: Not by your son.

29:33.815 --> 29:36.687
♪ There's an ally
you can trust ♪

29:36.818 --> 29:38.211
♪ Ooh ♪

29:38.341 --> 29:39.299
I'd think you'd be appalled

29:39.429 --> 29:40.648
to learn of his transgression.

29:40.779 --> 29:42.737
I know Herr Ruben in the party.

29:42.868 --> 29:44.347
I'm going to call him
immediately.

29:44.478 --> 29:46.175
-[ chokes ]
-INSPECTOR: I'm sure
your son will cooperate

29:46.306 --> 29:47.350
and he'll be returned
in no time.

29:47.481 --> 29:49.831
We are good socialists!
This is not right!

29:49.962 --> 29:51.354
-[ choking ]
-INSPECTOR: All this depends
on whether he names

29:51.485 --> 29:53.052
any of his cohorts.

29:53.182 --> 29:54.967
I have never been so insulted
in all my life!

29:55.097 --> 29:57.099
♪ He sends
his universal angels ♪♪

29:57.230 --> 29:58.361
-[ thumping ]
-INSPECTOR: And given
your party loyalty

29:58.492 --> 30:00.973
over the years,
I think you'd be...

30:01.103 --> 30:02.931
-YANEK: Isabell, please...
-Don't you dare speak to me.

30:03.062 --> 30:03.976
Not you. Not anymore.
-[ coughing, choking ]

30:04.106 --> 30:05.194
Mama?

30:05.325 --> 30:07.066
Mira, go back to bed.

30:07.196 --> 30:09.155
-Mama, look at Rainer!
-What? What happened?

30:09.285 --> 30:10.591
No! He's epileptic!

30:10.721 --> 30:11.940
He can't breathe!

30:12.071 --> 30:13.246
-Move out of the way!
-[ choking ]

30:13.376 --> 30:14.334
Call an ambulance!

30:14.464 --> 30:15.901
ISABELL:
Where's his medication?

30:16.031 --> 30:17.816
-It's okay, it's okay...
-ISABELL: Where is it?

30:17.946 --> 30:20.166
I can't find it!

30:20.296 --> 30:21.950
Just come and help, okay?
It's bad.

30:22.081 --> 30:24.910
It's okay...
Come help. Just come.

30:25.040 --> 30:26.737
-It's all going to be okay.
-ISABELL: Okay...

30:26.868 --> 30:28.000
[ Rainer choking ]

30:28.130 --> 30:30.176
YANEK:
It's okay...

30:30.306 --> 30:31.873
-Come on. It's okay...
-SOLDIER: We need an ambulance.

30:32.004 --> 30:32.961
A young man.
He's having a seizure.

30:33.092 --> 30:34.006
ISABELL:
Please, breathe.

30:34.136 --> 30:35.746
Breathe. Come on, breathe.

30:35.877 --> 30:37.009
-YANEK: Rainer...
-Breathe.

30:37.139 --> 30:39.011
-Rainer...
-ISABELL: Rainer.

30:39.141 --> 30:40.229
Rainer!

30:40.360 --> 30:42.144
[ echoing ]
Rainer!

30:42.275 --> 30:44.277
♪

31:10.520 --> 31:13.959
He should have been in the West.

31:14.089 --> 31:17.136
I'm sorry.

31:17.266 --> 31:19.094
It was too late.

31:22.402 --> 31:24.752
You murdered our son.

31:28.495 --> 31:30.279
[ Isabell sniffles ]

31:35.894 --> 31:38.070
Yanek? Is everything all right?

31:38.200 --> 31:39.071
MARTIN:
What's wrong?

31:44.815 --> 31:47.209
They came to you also.

31:47.340 --> 31:49.037
I'm calling Comrade Rubin.

31:49.168 --> 31:51.083
They won't be able
to hold him for long.

31:53.259 --> 31:56.784
Your son is still alive.

32:00.048 --> 32:04.096
Mira w-was the only one
who noticed, but...

32:05.271 --> 32:06.750
...she heard us too late.

32:06.881 --> 32:08.796
[ whimpers ]

32:12.365 --> 32:14.628
[ sobs ]

32:21.722 --> 32:24.246
YANEK:
There were now two worlds.

32:24.377 --> 32:27.206
[ lock clicks ]

32:27.336 --> 32:30.252
In mine, there was
nothing but grief.

32:32.559 --> 32:35.866
In his, the son I'd lost.

32:39.261 --> 32:41.263
RAINER PRIME:
I don't know.

32:41.394 --> 32:43.874
YOUNG MIRA PRIME: So why we
can't buy something...

32:44.005 --> 32:45.441
ISABELL PRIME:
You can eat apples.

32:45.572 --> 32:48.314
-I got apples. From Mrs. Kusner.
-Really?

32:48.444 --> 32:49.924
-Apples?
-Hey. Mm-hmm.

32:50.055 --> 32:52.231
Can we buy some apple juice?

32:52.361 --> 32:54.059
Maybe. Yeah.

32:54.189 --> 32:55.582
-[ laughs ]
-How was your day?

32:55.712 --> 32:57.366
-Good. How was yours?
-Mmm.

32:57.497 --> 32:58.715
Let's go to sleep.

33:13.469 --> 33:14.949
Mira.

33:22.913 --> 33:24.828
[ wheels squeaking ]

33:34.012 --> 33:36.362
Did you speak to Comrade Rubin?

33:37.580 --> 33:40.192
Rainer was released.

33:40.322 --> 33:42.281
Terrified.

33:42.411 --> 33:45.066
Said he would stop
associating with those friends.

33:45.197 --> 33:47.199
Isabell must be pleased.

33:49.418 --> 33:51.290
Yanek, I've been thinking.

33:51.420 --> 33:53.248
You haven't really lost him.

33:55.729 --> 33:59.037
There are things we could share.

34:03.650 --> 34:05.826
My son is dead.

34:21.407 --> 34:22.495
SPORTSCASTER [ on TV ]:
A great defense!

34:22.625 --> 34:23.844
[ man speaking rapidly on TV ]

34:27.108 --> 34:28.849
[ whistle blows ]

34:28.979 --> 34:30.894
[ news fanfare plays ]

34:33.288 --> 34:35.116
REPORTER [ on TV ]:
Following the historic decision

34:35.247 --> 34:37.031
made by the GDR just

34:37.162 --> 34:40.426
a few hours ago,
the borders of East Germany

34:40.556 --> 34:41.905
-have been opened.
-[ people cheer on TV ]

34:42.036 --> 34:43.298
Citizens from both sides

34:43.429 --> 34:44.995
have gathered along the Wall

34:45.126 --> 34:48.477
that has divided Berlin
for 28 years.

34:48.608 --> 34:51.001
Thousands of East Berliners
have already

34:51.132 --> 34:51.915
crossed the border tonight.

34:52.046 --> 34:54.092
♪

35:01.055 --> 35:02.970
[ panting ]

35:06.800 --> 35:08.671
MARTIN:
According to the records,

35:08.802 --> 35:10.456
the Fourth Floor was abandoned
years ago.

35:10.586 --> 35:12.022
Come.

35:12.153 --> 35:13.981
I want to show you something.

35:28.822 --> 35:32.042
Martin wants to meet us
on the Fourth Floor.

35:32.173 --> 35:33.566
Are you coming?

35:33.696 --> 35:36.569
I'm just going to finish up.

35:38.832 --> 35:40.355
MARTIN:
Used to be a dining room.

35:40.486 --> 35:43.924
Earliest days of the DDR.

35:44.054 --> 35:45.708
A power center.

35:45.839 --> 35:48.015
Martin, what are we doing here?

35:48.146 --> 35:50.191
I've been thinking...

35:50.322 --> 35:53.107
with the Wall down,
maybe it's time we expanded.

35:53.238 --> 35:55.414
Carefully, of course.

35:55.544 --> 35:57.938
What for, exactly?

35:58.068 --> 36:00.288
Research. Staff. Security.

36:00.419 --> 36:04.858
A new institute for the study
of this interchange.

36:23.311 --> 36:25.531
There's too many people.

36:25.661 --> 36:27.272
The secret would get out.

36:27.402 --> 36:28.708
He's right.

36:28.838 --> 36:31.754
But what if we separated
the floors?

36:31.885 --> 36:35.628
Each a different level
of clearance.

36:35.758 --> 36:37.586
They could study the secret

36:37.717 --> 36:40.241
without knowing
what they're studying.

36:40.372 --> 36:43.244
MARTIN: And this floor would be
ours alone.

36:43.375 --> 36:47.161
We could fill the halls
with our research.

36:54.342 --> 36:56.083
[ indistinct conversation
on TV]

37:08.791 --> 37:10.532
ISABELL PRIME:
Yanek?

37:10.663 --> 37:13.274
Hey. You're home early.

37:13.405 --> 37:16.146
Yeah.

37:16.277 --> 37:19.498
YOUNG MIRA PRIME:
Hello, Papa. A surprise.

37:19.628 --> 37:21.239
What's wrong?

37:21.369 --> 37:25.591
I'm just... happy to see you.

37:25.721 --> 37:27.201
RAINER PRIME:
Hey.

37:27.332 --> 37:28.333
Why are you home so early?

37:28.463 --> 37:31.466
My son.

37:31.597 --> 37:33.512
[ laughs ] Yeah? So?

37:34.687 --> 37:37.255
[ Rainer grunts ]

37:37.385 --> 37:39.953
Okay, Dad.

37:41.868 --> 37:45.567
No hug for me? [ laughs ]

37:45.698 --> 37:49.354
YANEK: On that day I betrayed
myself.

37:49.484 --> 37:51.138
And I knew I would do it again.

37:52.705 --> 37:54.707
♪

38:01.844 --> 38:03.324
[ vehicle motor rumbling ]

38:16.772 --> 38:18.600
[ indistinct chatter ]

38:23.083 --> 38:25.128
♪

38:28.218 --> 38:30.177
[ indistinct chatter ]

38:30.308 --> 38:32.005
WOMAN:
Yes, sir.

38:51.807 --> 38:53.200
Where is Yanek?

38:53.331 --> 38:56.334
I haven't seen him.

38:56.464 --> 38:58.771
Hey, guys, guys, guys, guys.
Please, please. Stop. Stop.

38:58.901 --> 39:01.164
If this disconnects,
we're set back six months.

39:01.295 --> 39:02.601
We must be gentle with it.

39:02.731 --> 39:03.993
Now let's do this slowly.

39:04.124 --> 39:06.082
♪

39:07.997 --> 39:10.043
[ laughs softly ]

39:29.802 --> 39:32.674
What has come over you
these days?

39:41.770 --> 39:43.729
♪

39:49.517 --> 39:52.172
[ indistinct P.A. announcement ]

39:56.481 --> 39:58.308
♪

40:02.400 --> 40:04.271
[ both moaning, panting ]

40:08.754 --> 40:12.410
YANEK: It was a compulsion
impossible to resist.

40:17.502 --> 40:22.376
To awake every day
in the cold prison of my world,

40:22.507 --> 40:26.424
and to flee it
for the warm embrace of his.

40:26.554 --> 40:29.427
[ both laugh ]

40:31.820 --> 40:34.344
How could I have been
so foolish...

40:34.475 --> 40:36.303
to assume it was just me?

40:36.434 --> 40:38.305
[ door closes]

40:43.963 --> 40:45.878
[ door opens]

40:46.008 --> 40:47.706
That was fast.

40:47.836 --> 40:49.534
Hmm?

40:49.664 --> 40:51.361
Did you forget what you were
going back for?

40:51.492 --> 40:53.363
Going back?

40:53.494 --> 40:55.365
[ refrigerator door opens,
glass clinks ]

40:55.496 --> 40:59.761
You said you forgot something
at the office.

40:59.892 --> 41:02.634
[ bottle open,
bottle cap rattles ]

41:08.727 --> 41:10.511
[ distant horns honking ]

41:15.603 --> 41:17.344
...and my other me
when I told that joke.

41:17.475 --> 41:19.346
[ indistinct chatter ]

41:28.921 --> 41:30.749
[ screeching nearby ]

41:38.104 --> 41:40.193
[ rats screeching ]

42:04.217 --> 42:06.393
Yes, there was
some irregularity.

42:06.524 --> 42:07.786
At the cellular level.

42:07.916 --> 42:10.005
One system collides
with the other,

42:10.136 --> 42:13.052
the environment changes, yes?

42:13.182 --> 42:15.707
Which means our immune systems
must be growing apart.

42:15.837 --> 42:17.491
Eh, it's too early to say that.

42:17.622 --> 42:19.711
It could be herd immunity.

42:19.841 --> 42:21.930
Some small variation
on a microcellular level.

42:22.061 --> 42:23.932
But our immunities do vary now.

42:24.063 --> 42:25.804
What are you asking me?

42:25.934 --> 42:28.546
Do you think it's possible...

42:28.676 --> 42:29.982
Two worlds.

42:30.112 --> 42:31.897
Twice the resources.

42:32.027 --> 42:34.029
If one world were to find itself
at a disadvantage,

42:34.160 --> 42:38.556
it would be inevitable that this
world would look to the other

42:38.686 --> 42:40.383
to better itself
at the other's expense.

42:40.514 --> 42:41.428
-No...
-It's instinctive.

42:41.559 --> 42:43.822
Marx. The species-being.

42:43.952 --> 42:45.040
Our needs and drives
were emancipated

42:45.171 --> 42:46.520
by the collective good.

42:46.651 --> 42:48.043
Who cares about
the collective good?

42:48.174 --> 42:50.306
The East is fucking dead now.

42:50.437 --> 42:53.135
What I'm saying is,

42:53.266 --> 42:56.748
the animalistic instincts
have won out.

42:56.878 --> 42:59.402
One side will always be tempted

42:59.533 --> 43:02.275
to eradicate the other.

43:02.405 --> 43:03.798
Yanek...

43:03.929 --> 43:05.800
If our immunologies
have grown different,

43:05.931 --> 43:09.499
there could be a strain
to affect them and not us.

43:09.630 --> 43:10.892
You're talking about a weapon.

43:11.023 --> 43:12.502
An insurance.

43:12.633 --> 43:13.765
For peace.

43:13.895 --> 43:17.072
Listen to yourself.

43:17.203 --> 43:20.075
A biological weapon of...

43:20.206 --> 43:21.381
It would never be used.

43:21.511 --> 43:24.340
Could never be used.

43:24.471 --> 43:25.733
Just a precaution.

43:25.864 --> 43:27.909
Then why would we need
such a thing?

43:30.042 --> 43:33.088
Because if we're having
this conversation...

43:33.219 --> 43:35.787
who's to say
they aren't having it, too?

43:41.836 --> 43:43.795
I'm going home. You coming?

43:43.925 --> 43:46.754
ILSE PRIME:
Might as well.

43:46.885 --> 43:50.715
-Good night.
-Good night.

43:50.845 --> 43:53.065
[ sighs ]

44:04.163 --> 44:06.382
I should be going also.

44:25.140 --> 44:27.577
♪

44:27.708 --> 44:29.623
[ keys jangle ]

44:33.322 --> 44:35.498
-Oh. Guten Abend.
-Guten Abend.

44:41.896 --> 44:43.071
Guten Abend.

44:48.250 --> 44:50.818
Hello?

44:53.299 --> 44:54.866
Anyone home?

44:57.346 --> 45:00.175
Mira said she'd be with friends.

45:00.306 --> 45:01.829
Rainer, too.

45:01.960 --> 45:04.049
Isabell has a class
at the university.

45:04.179 --> 45:07.879
I thought it might be
a good opportunity to speak.

45:36.255 --> 45:37.996
It's nice.

45:38.126 --> 45:40.085
Your home.

45:40.215 --> 45:42.609
Thank you.

45:47.135 --> 45:49.137
Mine's so empty.

45:49.268 --> 45:51.836
You should spend
more time there.

45:51.966 --> 45:55.622
I don't think they've missed me.

45:58.059 --> 46:00.192
Should I not have been
concerned?

46:00.322 --> 46:01.802
About your neglect?

46:01.933 --> 46:04.674
For Mira? For Isabell?

46:04.805 --> 46:07.199
How could I not want to look
after our family?

46:07.329 --> 46:10.158
Our family?

46:10.289 --> 46:12.682
They're my blood, too.

46:12.813 --> 46:14.772
And you've abandoned them.

46:14.902 --> 46:17.426
Do you think
you're better than me?

46:17.557 --> 46:20.995
[ scoffs ]
You're not well, comrade.

46:21.126 --> 46:22.605
Don't call me that.

46:22.736 --> 46:25.086
There are no comrades anymore.

46:25.217 --> 46:26.871
It was your idea.

46:27.001 --> 46:30.048
That first tape.

46:30.178 --> 46:33.051
I wonder if you knew, not giving
it to her, what it would mean.

46:33.181 --> 46:34.748
Don't be ridiculous.

46:34.879 --> 46:36.445
You wanted to be
different from me, hmm?

46:36.576 --> 46:38.273
-You didn't like what you saw.
-Of course not.

46:38.404 --> 46:39.753
That's the whole point.

46:39.884 --> 46:41.363
The only difference between us

46:41.494 --> 46:43.931
is such a stupid,
arbitrary thing.

46:44.062 --> 46:46.760
You experimented on me, and now
you're meddling with my life.

46:49.328 --> 46:50.938
Hmm.

46:59.555 --> 47:02.994
I found this lying around.

47:15.397 --> 47:19.053
Do you think I couldn't
smell you between my sheets?

47:21.795 --> 47:24.319
I offered her to you.

47:24.450 --> 47:27.235
You didn't have
to be secretive.

47:27.366 --> 47:29.368
Out of pity?

47:29.498 --> 47:32.023
We don't possess this matter.

47:32.153 --> 47:33.981
We share it.

47:34.112 --> 47:36.201
Stop it
with the fucking platitudes!

47:38.420 --> 47:40.161
Do you think I don't know
what you are doing?

47:40.292 --> 47:42.903
Your moral superiority,

47:43.034 --> 47:46.907
how it feels to offer me scraps
while you move into my life?

47:47.038 --> 47:49.301
YANEK PRIME: Rainer's death
was a tragedy, but

47:49.431 --> 47:50.911
you're letting it destroy you.

47:51.042 --> 47:52.739
Can you see that?

47:52.870 --> 47:55.307
We were friends before.

47:55.437 --> 47:57.439
And now you're being defeated
by these base,

47:57.570 --> 48:01.008
animal instincts, and I don't
know how to help you anymore.

48:01.139 --> 48:03.271
Don't look at me
with this superiority.

48:03.402 --> 48:06.187
I know your innermost thoughts.

48:06.318 --> 48:09.147
Did it arouse you

48:09.277 --> 48:12.063
to give her away?

48:12.193 --> 48:14.326
Like it aroused me to have her?

48:14.456 --> 48:16.328
That's enough.

48:16.458 --> 48:18.373
Stop denying what you are.

48:18.504 --> 48:21.420
I know what you are,
you son of a bitch.

48:21.550 --> 48:25.467
You were empty,
you had nothing to cling to,

48:25.598 --> 48:27.208
and you found purpose.

48:27.339 --> 48:29.384
You found it in me!

48:29.515 --> 48:31.734
-I want you out of my home.
-YANEK: It's my home, too.

48:31.865 --> 48:32.866
Isn't that what you said?

48:32.997 --> 48:34.389
I want you out! Out!

48:34.520 --> 48:36.696
-[ grunting ]
-Oh!

48:36.826 --> 48:38.741
[ Yanek Prime panting ]

48:38.872 --> 48:41.179
[ panting ]

48:41.309 --> 48:43.355
[ Yanek Prime groans softly ]

48:43.485 --> 48:45.748
I am sorry.

48:45.879 --> 48:48.360
[ grunting ]

48:48.490 --> 48:51.189
Yanek, don't.

48:51.319 --> 48:53.756
[ groaning ]

48:53.887 --> 48:56.194
[ yelps ]

48:56.324 --> 48:58.326
[ grunts ]

48:58.457 --> 49:00.372
[ soft groaning ]

49:04.898 --> 49:06.813
YANEK PRIME:
No! Wait!

49:08.423 --> 49:10.295
[ grunting ]

49:13.559 --> 49:16.170
[ gasping, groaning,
blows landing ]

49:17.345 --> 49:18.912
[ panting ]

49:19.043 --> 49:20.914
[ footsteps approaching ]

49:22.481 --> 49:24.874
Papa?

49:25.005 --> 49:26.789
[ whimpers ]

49:26.920 --> 49:28.269
What's going on?

49:30.358 --> 49:32.143
What is this?

49:32.273 --> 49:34.536
-YANEK: Mira...
-Get away from me.

49:34.667 --> 49:36.364
YANEK:
Mira, wait. Mira?

49:36.495 --> 49:38.018
YOUNG MIRA PRIME:
Get away! Help!

49:38.149 --> 49:39.889
-Somebody help!
-[ whimpers ]

49:45.112 --> 49:46.984
[ sighs ]

49:54.687 --> 49:57.429
-[ footsteps ]
-JUMA: Hello?

49:57.559 --> 49:59.909
[ footsteps ]

50:03.391 --> 50:05.350
Is someone there?

50:11.008 --> 50:13.184
Yanek?

50:16.143 --> 50:18.015
What's happened?

50:35.945 --> 50:37.556
[ door closes ]

50:37.686 --> 50:39.732
[ footsteps approaching ]

50:52.136 --> 50:54.007
The police are at his house.

50:55.530 --> 50:57.445
His daughter--

50:57.576 --> 50:59.404
she saw everything.

50:59.534 --> 51:02.798
He was wrong.

51:02.929 --> 51:05.584
We've both fallen.

51:05.714 --> 51:09.457
He gave into it, same as me.

51:09.588 --> 51:11.851
Stop it, Yanek!

51:11.981 --> 51:14.158
Goddamn you, shut up!

51:14.288 --> 51:16.899
[ sighs ]

51:17.030 --> 51:19.902
You've ruined everything.

51:20.033 --> 51:23.993
The experiment has failed.

51:24.124 --> 51:26.474
Don't you see?

51:26.605 --> 51:31.436
What happened to me
will happen to all of us.

51:31.566 --> 51:34.700
We can't remain
like this anymore.

51:34.830 --> 51:39.183
One will destroy the other.

51:39.313 --> 51:40.575
It's inevitable.

51:40.706 --> 51:42.403
You're wrong, Yanek.

51:42.534 --> 51:45.232
We just need
to restore the trust,

51:45.363 --> 51:48.409
which is why
this has to be done.

51:59.638 --> 52:00.900
What is this?

52:03.337 --> 52:07.385
You're being given
to their world as a prisoner.

52:07.515 --> 52:09.517
It's the only way
to keep the Crossing open.

52:09.648 --> 52:11.040
Take him, fast.

52:11.171 --> 52:12.694
Volker, please.

52:12.825 --> 52:15.044
-Please, Ilse.
-Please don't speak, Yanek.

52:15.175 --> 52:16.481
I did what any of us
would have done.

52:16.611 --> 52:18.352
No, we have to close the doors

52:18.483 --> 52:21.094
-before it's too late!
-[ speaking German ]

52:21.225 --> 52:23.749
This won't solve anything!

52:23.879 --> 52:27.231
You fucking idiots,
this won't change a thing!

52:30.277 --> 52:33.193
♪

52:52.821 --> 52:54.432
MIRA:
All the loose ends

52:54.562 --> 52:57.304
they had to tie up
because of what you did.

52:57.435 --> 53:01.221
I think he's run away
to Stockholm.

53:01.352 --> 53:04.398
I'm aware he had some business
over there.

53:06.313 --> 53:10.099
There might have been
another woman.

53:10.230 --> 53:13.364
If I hear anything,
I'll be in touch.

53:13.494 --> 53:15.844
I'm so sorry.

53:15.975 --> 53:18.717
MIRA:
It was hard for my other.

53:18.847 --> 53:22.590
It was harder for me.

53:22.721 --> 53:25.332
It was him.

53:25.463 --> 53:29.641
He ran past me
with blood on his hands.

53:29.771 --> 53:32.121
Rainer, do you believe me?

53:34.428 --> 53:36.691
Why won't you listen to me?

53:36.822 --> 53:39.390
Why won't anyone listen?

53:39.520 --> 53:41.392
It was him!

53:43.220 --> 53:46.788
-[ door slams ]
-She's not well.

53:46.919 --> 53:49.530
MIRA: And they went about
their business,

53:49.661 --> 53:51.750
thinking they had restored
some kind of peace.

53:51.880 --> 53:53.621
[ indistinct P.A. announcement ]

53:57.973 --> 54:01.063
MIRA:
But there was no peace anymore.

54:01.194 --> 54:04.937
Now, they feared each other.

54:06.678 --> 54:08.288
[ door opens ]

54:12.771 --> 54:15.295
It's just a precaution.

54:15.426 --> 54:18.342
It should never be used.

54:18.472 --> 54:22.433
Why do we need such a thing?

54:22.563 --> 54:26.219
Because if we're having
this conversation,

54:26.350 --> 54:28.221
then so are they.

54:32.269 --> 54:34.358
[ device hissing ]

54:47.849 --> 54:49.721
MIRA:
The precaution you proposed

54:49.851 --> 54:51.940
was released into our world.

54:52.071 --> 54:55.596
Accident or on purpose,
no one knows.

54:55.727 --> 54:58.643
It doesn't matter.

54:58.773 --> 55:03.343
By the time the flu spread,
the trust was gone.

55:03.474 --> 55:06.172
They developed new ways
to talk.

55:06.303 --> 55:08.653
[ case whirs, beeps ]

55:14.180 --> 55:16.138
No one can know

55:16.269 --> 55:18.097
where we reside.

55:18.227 --> 55:20.142
From this day forward,

55:20.273 --> 55:22.231
for our own protection.

55:24.669 --> 55:27.498
♪

55:46.778 --> 55:49.041
♪

56:05.623 --> 56:07.451
MIRA:
Now they live like hermits,

56:07.581 --> 56:10.541
talking to themselves
through this.

56:10.671 --> 56:13.718
Hiding their identities
for fear of reprisal.

56:13.848 --> 56:16.285
This is what you've left behind.

56:16.416 --> 56:18.766
Two broken worlds for me to fix.

56:18.897 --> 56:21.856
It-it didn't have to
be this way.

56:21.987 --> 56:24.206
I have ruined you.

56:24.337 --> 56:26.295
Ruined.

56:26.426 --> 56:29.081
That's what you see
when you look at me?

56:33.477 --> 56:35.609
What I witnessed that night,

56:35.740 --> 56:40.309
when you left my father dead
on that floor.

56:40.440 --> 56:42.790
I see the truth more
clearly than anyone.

56:42.921 --> 56:45.576
You will never get them
to close the doors forever.

56:45.706 --> 56:48.970
It would mean accepting failure.

56:49.101 --> 56:51.973
They will cling to this Crossing
until their dying breath.

56:52.104 --> 56:55.324
It took the socialists 40 years
to accept their experiment

56:55.455 --> 56:56.891
had failed, but they learned.

56:57.022 --> 57:00.460
[ scoffs ]
I spent decades in Echo.

57:00.591 --> 57:02.593
Harvesting human minds
for those bastards,

57:02.723 --> 57:04.464
and arguing, with every study,

57:04.595 --> 57:06.292
that what happened to me
was universal.

57:06.423 --> 57:07.380
They never listened.

57:07.511 --> 57:11.776
I listened, and I believe you.

57:14.561 --> 57:18.870
You and I, we are the only ones
who know the truth.

57:22.787 --> 57:25.529
I may not be
your real daughter, but...

57:25.659 --> 57:28.140
I've grown up in your image.

57:30.011 --> 57:34.363
And together we can
bring this war to an end.

57:36.496 --> 57:38.629
Will you gather them with me?

57:41.545 --> 57:43.372
[ humming, beeping ]

57:48.943 --> 57:50.771
[ static, interference ]

57:54.819 --> 57:57.386
I know you are out there,

57:57.517 --> 57:59.824
and you're listening to me now.

58:02.522 --> 58:05.046
You are so blind.

58:05.177 --> 58:06.918
The blood of millions
is on your hands,

58:07.048 --> 58:09.355
and I won't stand by any longer.

58:09.486 --> 58:11.923
My terms are simple.

58:12.053 --> 58:14.621
Shut down the Crossing forever.

58:14.752 --> 58:18.190
I want you to invite our
neighbors for a meeting.

58:18.320 --> 58:20.758
Tomorrow, I will surrender
myself and my father

58:20.888 --> 58:23.630
to your custody.

58:23.761 --> 58:27.982
I want to meet all of you.
Together.

58:28.113 --> 58:30.376
The choice is yours.

58:37.775 --> 58:39.690
♪

59:09.807 --> 59:11.722
♪
